transcript:
if you always worry about what other
people think of you and you never feel
good enough here's one thing you can do
that people often learn in therapy
stop trying to control the
uncontrollable and instead
focus on what you can control like what
you think of you ask yourself am i the
kind of person that i like do i approve
of me when you can honestly answer those
questions with a yes then disapproval
from others still stings but it's much
easier to deal with
